Anthony Joshua says he is prepared for his heavyweight title fight against Kubrat Pulev on Saturday to go to the "final bell" as he returns to the ring after a 12-month absence.
The British boxer will be in action for the first time since he outpointed Andy Ruiz Jr in Saudi Arabia to regain the WBA, WBO and IBF belts he lost to the same opponent at Madison Square Garden in June 2019.



