The Bulgarian's only defeat came in a world title fight against Wladimir Klitschko in 2014.
"I'm ready for this fight. We spend a long time waiting because 2017 I had a problem and that is why I tell my trainer we must go for the win," he said.
"That is why I said 'let's not fight now (in 2017)' because I believed this fight would come again one day and I'm here now, ready to fight good and ready to win." He allegedly received a sh200,000 bribe to approve the opening of a fuel station in Oyugis. Kabila had succeeded in forming an army with many generals said to still be loyal to him. This is the first time Uhuru is meeting Abiy since Addis Ababa launched a crackdown on TPLF.